With a strong commitment to innovation and sustainability, Braskem has been at the forefront of developing cutting-edge solutions to meet the evolving needs of the market and address the challenges posed by climate change and plastic waste. Their focus on research and development has led to the introduction of bio-based materials with enhanced properties, such as increased biodegradability and improved durability, thus expanding the scope of applications for bioplastics and biopolymers. By investing in new technologies and strategic partnerships, Braskem continues to drive advancements in sustainable materials that contribute to a circular economy model and support the transition towards a more environmentally friendly future.

Furthermore, Braskem's initiatives extend beyond product innovation, encompassing sustainable practices throughout their operations and supply chain. Through initiatives like the Life Cycle Assessment (LCA) methodology, Braskem evaluates the environmental impacts of its products from raw material sourcing to end-of-life disposal, ensuring transparency and accountability in their sustainability efforts. By adopting a holistic approach to sustainability, Braskem aims to minimize its carbon footprint, promote resource efficiency, and foster a culture of responsible consumption and production within the industry.

